---
import Breadcrumbs from '@/components/Breadcrumbs.astro'
import PageHead from '@/components/PageHead.astro'
import { SITE } from '@/consts'
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro'

// Person Schema for About page
const personSchema = {
	'@context': 'https://schema.org',
	'@type': 'Person',
	name: SITE.title,
	url: SITE.href,
	description: SITE.description
}
---

<Layout class="max-w-3xl">
	<PageHead slot="head" title="About" />

	<!-- Person Schema for About page SEO -->
	<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(personSchema)} />

	<Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'About', icon: 'lucide:user' }]} />

	<section class="flex flex-col gap-8">
		<!-- Header -->
		<div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
			<div>
				<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold md:text-4xl">About</h1>
				<p class="text-muted-foreground mt-1 font-mono text-sm">
					Learn more about this blog
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- Main Content -->
		<div class="prose prose-sm dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6">
			<p class="text-foreground text-lg leading-relaxed">
				<strong class="text-primary">Vivi</strong> — also known as chadisfaction —
				is a developer, systems architect, and digital insurgent operating from the
				intersection of AI, activism, and code craft.
			</p>

			<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
				This isn't a resume. It's a manifesto. I'm not here to impress
				recruiters with buzzwords or chase the next VC-backed hype cycle. I'm
				here to build technology that matters — systems that understand human
				nuance, platforms that empower the marginalized, and discourse that
				challenges the status quo.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-foreground mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">
				The Digital Empire
			</h2>

			<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
				I operate a constellation of domains, each serving a distinct purpose:
			</p>

			<ul class="text-muted-foreground space-y-2">
				<li>
					<a
						href="https://gemcity.xyz"
						class="text-foreground hover:text-primary font-bold transition-colors"
						>gemcity.xyz</a
					> — This nexus. Thought leadership, tech discourse, and the home base.
				</li>
				<li>
					<a
						href="https://pixelatedempathy.com"
						class="text-foreground hover:text-primary font-bold transition-colors"
						>pixelatedempathy.com</a
					> — Enterprise-grade AI for emotional intelligence. The flagship.
				</li>
				<li>
					<a
						href="https://chadisfaction.tech"
						class="text-foreground hover:text-primary font-bold transition-colors"
						>chadisfaction.tech</a
					> — Technical playground and development projects.
				</li>
				<li>
					<a
						href="https://acab.lol"
						class="text-foreground hover:text-primary font-bold transition-colors"
						>acab.lol</a
					> — Security research and activist technology.
				</li>
				<li>
					<a
						href="https://vivi.rocks"
						class="text-foreground hover:text-primary font-bold transition-colors"
						>vivi.rocks</a
					> — Creative outlet for music, art, and unfiltered expression.
				</li>
				<li>
					<a
						href="https://bantesla.lol"
						class="text-foreground hover:text-primary font-bold transition-colors"
						>bantesla.lol</a
					> — Critical analysis of tech culture and corporate mythology.
				</li>
			</ul>

			<h2 class="text-foreground mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">What I Believe</h2>

			<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
				Technology should empower the marginalized, not entrench the powerful.
				Code is a tool of liberation when wielded with intention. AI and LLMs
				represent unprecedented potential — but only if we resist the urge to
				automate oppression.
			</p>

			<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
				The best systems are built by people who question the systems they're
				building. Every line of code is a political act. Every API endpoint
				shapes behavior. Every algorithm encodes values.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-foreground mt-8 text-xl font-semibold">
				What You'll Find Here
			</h2>

			<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
				Sharp analysis of AI/LLM technology without the hype. Critical
				examinations of tech culture. Practical guides for building systems that
				matter. Occasional rants about the surveillance state. Musings on the
				intersection of code and creativity.
			</p>

			<p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
				No corporate fluff. No tech-bro optimism. Just rigorous thinking about
				where technology is taking us — and whether we should be going there at
				all.
			</p>

			<div class="border-border mt-8 border-t pt-6">
				<p class="text-muted-foreground text-sm italic">
					"The best code is written with one eye on the compiler and the other
					on the society it will shape."
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
